Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.08,0:00:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome to Dr. David Hawkins Sedona 2002\Nseries, The Way to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.40,0:00:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Lecture 6, Realizing the Root of\NConsciousness:
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.35,0:00:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Meditative and Contemplative Techniques.\NOriginally presented in June of 2002 at
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.32,0:00:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the Sedona Creative Life Center.\NI I was never very happy about this
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.20,0:00:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,physicality. As I was saying, it's\Nsuddenly at age three out of out of
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.20,0:00:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,oblivion\Nand I'm a great enthusiast of oblivion.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.00,0:00:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of oblivion, there was the shock of\Nthis v thisness. Oh my god, it was
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.12,0:01:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,awful.\NAnd uh so we're all set to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.07,0:01:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,>> All right. Uh out of happy oblivion,\Nthere was suddenly thisness.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.24,0:01:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh and thisness has been like a plague\Never since.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.08,0:01:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,To get beyond thisness,\Nthis uh physicality which people um
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.92,0:01:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,strangely become enamored of. I don't\Nknow. They seem like they suffer from
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.00,0:01:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,some kind of insanity that they enjoy\Nthis thing. But
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.64,0:01:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,with a great deal of endeavor, you can\Nget it to be an enjoyable mechanism.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.43,0:01:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And um so it's a big rag doll that I've\Nbeen putting up with all these years.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.04,0:01:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,This week I was 75. So for 72 years I've\Nputting up with this thing, which has
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.40,0:01:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,certainly earned me the karma of getting\Nrid of it someday.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.36,0:01:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,uh the good karma of getting rid of it\Nsomeday. Um so that's somewhat different
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.72,0:01:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,than a lot of people look at the whole\Nsituation.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.24,0:02:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh but apparently that came out of some\Nlifetimes of as a hinyana Buddhist I was
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.07,0:02:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,a very devout Buddhist monk and um the\Nultimate reality was voidness and
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.72,0:02:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,consequently when I went out of body it\Nwent into void and don't remember
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.20,0:02:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,anything\Ndon't remember nothing till you come
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.31,0:02:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,back in the next lifetime and uh but as\Nyou reach a certain level of awareness
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.08,0:02:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,you remember the previous lifetimes and\Nuh Uh they they all string together like
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.31,0:02:34.95,Default,,0,0,0,,frankly like it's like this lifetime.\NIt's it's it's all the same lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.95,0:02:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh but it was we I was just looking at a\Ncouple of them yesterday cuz something
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.51,0:02:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,came up about them. And you saw almost\Nthe flip-flop nature, one lifetime being
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.51,0:02:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,this and creating all kinds of negative\Nbad karma, then the next lifetime
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.51,0:02:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,flopping over to undo all that. I said,\N"Whoa, that was really very interesting
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.44,0:03:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,how they're tied together.\NWell, today we're talking about um
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.84,0:03:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,let's see what are we talking about\Ntoday. Today's lecture is um oh
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.44,0:03:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,meditation. Yes.\NToday's meditation.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.72,0:03:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But first we sort of start out by um\Nyou know um validating the reality in
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.80,0:03:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,which we are here this morning\Nin which everything is occurring of its
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.23,0:03:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,own.\NYou realize that nothing is causing
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.31,0:03:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,anything else.\NThat was the first lecture
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.79,0:03:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,to transcend the whole illusion of\Ncausality
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.04,0:03:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,because that is the whole structure of\Nthe ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.51,0:03:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It sees everything is causing everything\Nelse and becomes entrapped by that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.04,0:03:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,All the ego mechanisms are laid somehow\Non causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.76,0:03:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Something out there is causing me to\Nfeel this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.84,0:04:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,um we see oursel as the victims of some\Nmysterious force called cause
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.00,0:04:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of seeing ourself as the context\Nin which we witness all that. So we
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.20,0:04:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,start out the lectures by just recalling\Nthat nothing is causing anything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.60,0:04:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is occurring spontaneously\Nas the fulfillment of the expression of
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.24,0:04:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,its own essence from moment to moment.\NSo
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.60,0:04:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,if we're stuck in the word cause then\Nwe'll move up to cause and then we'll
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.04,0:04:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,move beyond cause. If we are going to\Nstick with the word cause then we see
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.08,0:04:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,that there's only one cause for\Neverything
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.24,0:04:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and that cause is the cause of every\Ninstant.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.12,0:05:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The cause of the hand being where it is\Nis the total action of the entire
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.47,0:05:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,universe since the beginning of time\Nmanifesting itself via the will of God
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.00,0:05:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,by divine ordinance as creation.\NAnd out of creation arises the essence.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.16,0:05:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And the essence out of the energy of\Ncreation then expresses itself as the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.75,0:05:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,fulfillment of its essence.\NThe cause of this instant is exactly the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.84,0:05:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,same as the cause of this instant is\Nexactly the same as the cause of this
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.68,0:05:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,instant. And that is the totality of the\Nentire universe since the beginning of
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.08,0:05:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,all of time.\NSo that every instant is the fulfillment
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.00,0:05:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,of the creative potential potential of\NGod manifesting as the essence of th
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.68,0:05:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that which this is fulfills the\Npotentiality of its essence which in the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.56,0:06:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,case of a hand is to move forward\Nseemingly in space. So if we jump the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.16,0:06:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,presumption that there's something\Ncausing it to do that
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.40,0:06:13.75,Default,,0,0,0,,then we see that with absolute freedom\Nthe universe is merely
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.75,0:06:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,like a flower being what it is. You see\Nthe flower
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.47,0:06:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,this instant doesn't cause the flower to\Ngrow. This instant it doesn't cause the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.96,0:06:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,flower. flower is unfolding its infinite\Npotentiality of being a flower has the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.36,0:06:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,fulfillment of its divine design.\NNothing is causing it to do that. The
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.00,0:06:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,sun doesn't cause it to do that. The\Nrain doesn't cause it to do that. The
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.08,0:06:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,seed doesn't cause it to do that.\NPutting it in your window in a pot
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.08,0:06:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't cause the flower to do that. The\Nflower is doing it of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.24,0:06:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's fulfilling\Nthe destiny, the potential destiny of
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.68,0:07:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,its own essence.\NConsequently, at every second at which
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.88,0:07:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,it is doing that, it is absolutely\Nperfect. At this moment, it's perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.24,0:07:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,At this moment, it's perfect because\Nperfection is that it should do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.91,0:07:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And because it is doing that at every\Nmoment, it is the perfect fulfillment of
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.08,0:07:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the will of God.\NTherefore, the entire universe stands in
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.88,0:07:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,absolute perfection from instant to\Ninstant.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.12,0:07:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NThank you, God, for saying that. I mean,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.52,0:07:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I never could have said that.\NThat was cool, man.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.59,0:07:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,But that is the way it is.\NWhen you first see that, it lays you
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.87,0:07:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,out.\NWhen you first walk into that and it
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.56,0:08:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,reveals itself.\NIf you can function for a few years, you
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.68,0:08:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,can't function for some years actually,\Nsome years before one could function
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.40,0:08:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,again\Nbecause um all is happening of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.19,0:08:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the freedom that arises from that\Nrealization,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.24,0:08:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,how to how to how to arrive at that\Nrealization
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.68,0:08:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,is what we're talking about today. We're\Ntalking about meditation, one of the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.91,0:08:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,great timehonored traditions\Nand ways to the awareness of the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.80,0:08:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,presence of God.\NNow
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.80,0:08:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,meditation itself is an enormous\Nsubject.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.95,0:08:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure we could fill this whole book\Nwith all the books written on meditation
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.04,0:08:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout the centuries.\Nthe great gurus, the great teachers of
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.20,0:09:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,meditation, the meditation centers,\Nthe Buddhist traditions, um yoga, the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.76,0:09:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Indian Aryan traditions\Nand in the far east of course there's
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.44,0:09:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,enormous um\Namount of literature and training.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.48,0:09:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Meditation need not be in the in the\Ncontext of any particular religion or
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.39,0:09:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual teaching.\NMedit uh friends of ours in Korea, Dr.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.32,0:09:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Moon has a meditation center. And you\Nask her, is it Christian? No. Is it
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.36,0:09:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Buddhist? No. Is it Hindu? No. What is\Nit? It's a meditation center. She says,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.92,0:09:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,you get it. Oh,\Nyou just go there and meditate. Oh, wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.80,0:09:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, the process itself\Nthen unfolds
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.12,0:09:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,through the inner layers of the ego. You\Ntranscend the ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.12,0:10:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So let's talk a little bit\Nabout the various techniques.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.20,0:10:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Um\Nmany of which of course are well
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.04,0:10:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,established in the literature\Nhave uh specific training programs.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.92,0:10:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Many become very um detailed in posture,\Ndiet, breathing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.88,0:10:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Many are accompanied by complicated\Nbreathing mechanisms.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.76,0:10:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,There's all kinds of incredible\Nmeditative techniques.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.04,0:10:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We're not going to talk about them today\Nbecause the world's literature is full
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.95,0:10:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,of instructions,\Ninstruction centers, traditions,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.48,0:10:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,postures, breathing exercises,\Npranayyana.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.27,0:10:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll talk more about the essence of the\Nmeditative process itself, which is
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.48,0:10:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,common to all of them.\NAnd because most of the people here, you
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.12,0:11:00.95,Default,,0,0,0,,see, it's very neat to be able to shave\Nyour head, leave the world, join a Zen
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.95,0:11:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,monastery,\Nand sit zen
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.72,0:11:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,for 10 or 20 years. I love it.\NIt pulls pulls me. I have to resist it
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.27,0:11:20.07,Default,,0,0,0,,all the time. It's a natural state. The\Nnatural state. And anything else in a
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.07,0:11:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,way is sort of a drag.\Nand I was the psychiatric consultant to
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.07,0:11:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the Zen uh\Nmonastery in New York. It was up in the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.76,0:11:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,little mountains right near New York\NCity. I forget where it is. Anyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.80,0:11:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and uh I used to go to the Frisen\NInstitute in New York City.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.00,0:11:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Um so meditation itself even you know as\Na lifestyle is extremely attractive.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.72,0:12:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The average person here today is not\Nable to do that. And
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.76,0:12:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,consequently, how can we obtain the\Nbenefits of meditation
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.48,0:12:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,uh without um ren without going through\Nformal renunciation?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.04,0:12:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And we'll talk a little bit today about\Nrenunciation. Don't let me forget to
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.88,0:12:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,talk about renunciation.\NUm all right. So what meditative
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.32,0:12:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,awareness can we have\Nwalking about and functioning within the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.39,0:12:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,ordinary world?\NAnd so we'll talk about generally two
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.51,0:12:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,styles of meditation\Nand we'll talk about um ways to
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.63,0:12:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,transcend the mind.\NUh so it'll be a busy morning. Yes. Come
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.51,0:12:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,think of it\Nnow. I started to think again myself. I
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.32,0:12:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,say, "Whoa, you got to go through all\Nthat, right?" Yes,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.36,0:13:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,we got all that stuff there. Well,\Nlet's start with a generality that um
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.51,0:13:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,there is content\Nand there is context.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.07,0:13:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Context, you know, totally changes\Ncontent.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.04,0:13:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And a great deal of\Nerror arises in not being aware of the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.36,0:13:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,relationship of content and context.\NWhat we're looking for in meditation is
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.72,0:13:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,how to transcend content and realize\Nthat the self that which we are is the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.68,0:13:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,context.\NAnd how can we do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.88,0:13:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,There's two ways. one I call macular\Nfocus which is central focus intense
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.39,0:13:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,fixity on the content of aware of the\Nego on the content of what you're
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.39,0:13:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,looking at and doing\Nand the other is what I would call
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.80,0:14:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,peripheral peripheral vision if we\Ncompare it to vision the macula is that
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.32,0:14:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,uh phobia in the back of the retina that\Nfocuses very specifically on details
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.80,0:14:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,if you Look at the a fly and then you\Nfocus on the eye of the fly. Then you
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.36,0:14:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,are being very specific and focusing on\Na very very small concentrated area.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.56,0:14:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,That's sort of macular vision.\NThen we have peripheral vision
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.63,0:14:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,because although I can see the content\Nof what is in front of my eyes,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.72,0:14:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,there is a greater generality.\NA person who's interested in spiritual
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.36,0:14:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,evolution learns\Nto focus the sense of self,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.24,0:14:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the sense of awareness,\Num the alertness
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.16,0:15:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,um progressively more and more to the\Nperipheral vision.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.27,0:15:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,One becomes quite peripheral\Nin experiencing the world from moment to
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.19,0:15:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,moment.\NOne is aware of the general context.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.88,0:15:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Um now the general context out of which\Nthe world seems to arise or appear
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.12,0:15:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,uh is silent and invisible.\NSo the ultimate context then is the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.36,0:15:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,silent invisibility almost the space and\Nsilence out of which experience
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.27,0:15:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,which allows experience to be possible.\NIf it is not for the background of
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.76,0:15:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,silence you cannot hear these words.\NIf it is not for the emptiness and
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.63,0:15:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,infinite, you might say no thingness of\Nspace, you would not be able to observe
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.48,0:16:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,uh physicality. You couldn't see\Nbuildings or
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.04,0:16:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,persons\Nto be at aware at all times
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.16,0:16:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,of the infinite space, the infinite\Npotentiality
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.63,0:16:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,out of which this moment seems to be\Narising
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.07,0:16:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,is somewhat aligned with the awareness\Nthat all is happening of its own. that
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.83,0:16:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,everything is spontaneously\Noccurring
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.00,0:16:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,without any intervention\Nwithout any causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.19,0:16:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It's as though there is an infinite\Nconcert in which everything is happening
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.16,0:16:51.75,Default,,0,0,0,,spontaneously of its own and one is the\Nwitness of what appears to be happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.75,0:16:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,This can be done formally in seated\Nmeditation and we'll get to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.83,0:17:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We're trying to talk about how to reach\Na higher state of awareness
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.19,0:17:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,even though one is functioning in the\Nworld. You begin you begin to witness
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.64,0:17:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,that everything is happening of its own\Nand that there is no nothing causing it
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.31,0:17:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,to be that way.\NSo we be as you transcend cause you you
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.16,0:17:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you then become aware that everything is\Nhappening
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.00,0:17:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,spontaneously.\NIf we sit down to meditate let's say we
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.08,0:17:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,sit down to meditate\Nthe problem is almost always the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.20,0:17:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,thinkingness of the mind.\NSo we'll talk now more about the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.52,0:17:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,meditative process in a formal sense.\NYou know, Ramana Maharshi always
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.67,0:17:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,recommended um that he he always said\Nyou don't have to join a monastery to
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.72,0:18:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,become enlightened. You that the\Nhouseholder can go about his business
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.40,0:18:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and all he has to do is keep in mind in\Nthe back of his mind at all times who am
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.28,0:18:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I?\NSo
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.52,0:18:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I never agreed with who am I.\NThe experiential
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.20,0:18:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,awareness here is more what am I?\NSeemed to me who am I which was not
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.79,0:18:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,notoriously successful either as a\Nmantra.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.00,0:18:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,uh that whom am I focuses\Nyou to look for another illusion,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.91,0:18:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,another\Ndefinition, another pronoun of self.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.20,0:18:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is experienced as\Nthe identity with the personal is
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.60,0:18:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,transcended is a wheness not a\Nwhesseness.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.12,0:18:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The wetness has the peculiarity of sense\Nof self with the capital S but that self
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.84,0:19:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,is the allness of everythingness and\Nit's really beyond whesseness.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.08,0:19:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Um\Nsome people who had been there to
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.12,0:19:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,his ashram even after he died you know\Nuh had said that there was not a great
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.84,0:19:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,deal of success with that method and I\Nalso thought it's due to the whess
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.76,0:19:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than the whatness. We'll explain\Nthe wetness today to try and clarify
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.16,0:19:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,what I just said. Let's see. Can we turn\Non this mystery machine here?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.88,0:19:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah h\Nall right. So as you either either
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.55,0:19:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you're in seated meditation\Nor as you're walking about in the world
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.88,0:19:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,because as you progress in spiritual\Nwork the two are not different. The two
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.72,0:19:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,become the same.\Num because all of life because of the
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.12,0:20:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,way you recontextualize your life\Nbecomes a meditation.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.36,0:20:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So on its highest level then a\Nmeditation is merely the manner in which
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.32,0:20:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,you contextualize your experience of\Naliveness.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.16,0:20:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,If you contextualize\Nevery instant of your existence as a
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.16,0:20:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,dedicated dedication to the realization\Nof God, all of your your entire life
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.12,0:20:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes a meditation. So we cannot\Nseparate out meditation as this and the
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.03,0:20:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,you is that and this and that.\NMeditation then is a way of
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.20,0:20:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,contextualizing your life.\NLet's say from a greater context. from a
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.20,0:20:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,greater context.\NWhat is witnessed then
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.20,0:21:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the body walking around on the stage\Nwhich is a peculiarity actually
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.64,0:21:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,is merely the content of a field. So\Nlet's look at the field. Let's look at
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.84,0:21:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,the field itself. It seems to be warped,\Ndoesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.60,0:21:22.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't we pull this open farther? Let's\Nsee.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.79,0:21:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know how you work this machine.\NAnybody know how to rip? I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.91,0:21:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you make it not do that? Well,\Nit's crooked. So, there's nothing we can
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.60,0:21:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,do about it.\NIt's crooked. Somebody will know how to
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.79,0:21:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,fix that.\NAnd we won't worry about it till
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.84,0:21:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,somebody does.\NAll right. So the progressive fields of
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.28,0:21:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,realization\Nwhether you're walking about in a
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.64,0:21:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,walking meditation throughout life\Nor whether you're seated and
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.40,0:21:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,cross-legged\Ndoing very specific breathing
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.36,0:22:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,picturing the energy flowing up your\Nspine to the crown chakra and up to the
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.48,0:22:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,higher levels\Nas light
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.20,0:22:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,now or whether you're walking around in\Nthe world
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.00,0:22:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the first thing that you experience is\Nform
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.55,0:22:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and a person sits down and they say well\NI can't seem to get it any place with
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.32,0:22:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,meditation\Nbecause the minute I sit down the mind
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.32,0:22:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the thoughts are racing around the\Nthoughts the distractions of the world
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.64,0:22:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and so the average person the average\Nperson's life then is focused on thought
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.03,0:22:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,form.\NThe person bewills the fact that no
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.84,0:23:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,matter what they do, their mind seems to\Nbe focused on
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.84,0:23:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,a passing panorama of endless thoughts\Nand feelings and form.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.64,0:23:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So that is the first thing we notice.\NNow because this form is endless the
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.36,0:23:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,content of thinkingness is endless.\NIt goes on spontaneously.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.52,0:23:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The first thing to notice about it is\Nit's got nothing to do with you because
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.91,0:23:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,you can tell it to stop and it won't.\NWell, if you were if that's what you
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.55,0:23:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,were and you told it to stop, it would\Ninstantly stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.96,0:23:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So you tell your mind stop.\Ngoes right on thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.55,0:23:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems to be quite unruly.\NThose are those are the famous ox
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.03,0:23:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,hurting pictures. You know, the first\Npicture shows the ox, the wild ox.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.40,0:24:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's the wild untamed mind. And um\Nthe naive person thinks well I have to
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.32,0:24:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,um\Ndeal with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.72,0:24:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,No happily you don't have to deal with\Nthe content of mind
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.08,0:24:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,because the only thing you have to\Nnotice about it is that what it's doing
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.52,0:24:26.79,Default,,0,0,0,,it's doing spontaneously.\NIt's not the content of mind that's
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.79,0:24:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,interesting at all. What is of interest\Nis the process of mind. It's going on of
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.79,0:24:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,its own. Had nothing to do with you.\NCouldn't care less about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.67,0:24:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll say very nasty things about you.\NYou know what the mind does?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.48,0:24:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You're guilty. You're weak. You're\Nyou're wasting your money. You're creep.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.64,0:25:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't trust the mind at all. It's\Nnot even your It's not even your friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.03,0:25:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not even a friend. I mean, it\Ndoesn't It just goes on and willy-nilly
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.03,0:25:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,says all kinds of When it runs out of\Nthoughts, it'll say
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.24,0:25:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,you picture some erotic scene from some\Nmovie when you were a teenager.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.84,0:25:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll think of something horrible about\Nthe future.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.00,0:25:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my.\NWhen the mind gets threatened with no
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.40,0:25:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,thoughts, it really gets wild. It'll\Njust do anything crazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.96,0:25:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of stabbing yourself or something,\Nyou know. It'll just do anything bizarre
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.64,0:25:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,to keep going. Well,\Nso when you look at the mind, then don't
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.96,0:25:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,be don't be bothered with it. It's an\Nendless fantasmagoria.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.20,0:25:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I like that word, fantasmagoria.\NIt just proliferates endless BS. You
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.12,0:26:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,know what it's doing.\NOccasionally, occasionally under very
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.79,0:26:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,favorable circumstances with great focus\Nand effort, you can get it to stop all
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.36,0:26:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,that and be logically form a logical\Nsequence for a short period of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.44,0:26:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and do what's called thinking.\NMost of the time it's thoughting. It's
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.91,0:26:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,not thinking. It's thoughting and\Nimaging. All right. So thinking it does
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.64,0:26:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,really quite rarely. Should I turn left\Nat the next corner? It's through
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.36,0:26:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,thinking. Now it's not going to think\Nfor another 20 minutes probably. Where
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.55,0:26:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,should I park? That's the next time it\Nthinks. What was it doing during that 20
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.88,0:26:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,minutes? It was\NFeed fishies in a nitty bitty boo.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.03,0:26:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,That's that's the one my mind used to\Nlike. Feed the fishies in a nitty bitty
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.27,0:27:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,boo.\NAll right. So form then the content is
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.55,0:27:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,not of any interest. Now many people\Nspend endless spiritual lifetimes trying
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.12,0:27:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,to change form.\NYou realize how many spiritual programs
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.72,0:27:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,have to do with form. Don't think this,\Nthink that. Recontextualize it this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.32,0:27:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't think of its opposite. You know,\Nprefix it with if but yes or no.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.12,0:27:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Trying to change form is not going to\Nwork
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.55,0:27:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,because the ego, the mind is\Nuh like the heartbeat destined to do
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.40,0:27:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,what it does.\NWhy should the mind stop thinking then
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.64,0:27:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,when that's what it's supposed to do?\NAll right. So, what does one realize out
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.96,0:27:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,of this?\NIf you watch the content of mind going
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.44,0:28:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,by willy-nilly like a mad cap insane\Nasylum, you realize that you are not the
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.36,0:28:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,mind. If you were the mind and you told\Nit to stop, it could stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.52,0:28:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And we notice then the first most\Nimportant thing that's going to take us
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.36,0:28:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,out of it is that it's impersonal.\NThe most stunning thing to learn about
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.15,0:28:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,witnessing the content of your mind is\Nthat it's impersonal.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.20,0:28:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Like the heartbeat, like breathing,\Nlike your toenails growing, it's
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.64,0:28:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,impersonal. Doesn't ask you about it.\NYour toenails don't say, "Should I grow
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.88,0:28:42.08,Default,,0,0,0,,this month?\NIt's a sort of a physiologic spontaneous
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.08,0:28:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,activity thinking this. So don't be\Ndisturbed about it because
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.32,0:28:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,uh it's doing what it's supposed to do.\NYou can't really be worried about the
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.72,0:28:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,content about it because no matter what\Ntrick you try with the content, it's
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.20,0:29:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,smarter than you will and it would trick\Nyou in some other way. You say don't
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.27,0:29:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,think about this good doesn't he thinks\Nabout that instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.48,0:29:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So, the first thing you\Nnotice is that it's endless form and
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.08,0:29:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,it's unstoppable.\NTrying to silence your mind is idiotic.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.52,0:29:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And millions of people do that all the\Ntime. Trying to go to sleep at night and
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.39,0:29:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,they're trying to stop their mind from\Nthinking. Uh
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.72,0:29:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,what you notice is that it's impersonal.\NIt does what it's doing of its own. H
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.52,0:29:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,wow. So you stop identifying with the\Ncontent of thought is me. It's not me.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.79,0:29:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I can put you under hypnosis, program\Nyour mind. You wake up, you think all
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.15,0:29:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that. You think I thought that. You\Ndidn't think that, idiot. I thought it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.00,0:29:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So the first thing we can\Nnotice, how do you know what the mind is
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.76,0:29:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,thinking?\NHow do you know? How do you know what
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.27,0:30:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,what is this? How do you know what's on\Non that channel? You know it because
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.64,0:30:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,it's registering. It's registering.\NAh, so we're out of the content of mind
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.52,0:30:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and now and well they say if I'm not the\Nprogram
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.08,0:30:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,then maybe I'm the BCR. Well, you're\Ngetting closer.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.72,0:30:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We're aware of what's going on in mind\Nbecause it's registering somewhere. It's
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.84,0:30:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,registering somewhere in consciousness.\Nand it's being recognized.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.39,0:30:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the functions of\Nyou see this mind is doing what it's
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.52,0:30:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,doing but that's not what's bothering\Nyou. What's bothering you is that you're
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.24,0:30:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,registering it. You're aware of it.\NYou're recognizing it. And who is doing
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.15,0:30:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that?\NThe watcher is doing that. The
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.96,0:31:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,experiencer is experiencing that the\Nmind is doing all that.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.52,0:31:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you know that the experiencer is\Nexperiencing? Because there's a watcher
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.36,0:31:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,experiencing it. And below that there is\Nawareness.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.15,0:31:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So the identifications of who I am first\Nas we sit in meditation or as we go
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.32,0:31:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,about the day\Nis not the content of thought. It's not
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.15,0:31:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the content of feeling or thought or\Nimaginations or memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.52,0:31:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to do with closer with some\Nimpersonal function called registering.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.96,0:31:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Even the recognition\Nof if you recognize a monkey as a
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.67,0:31:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,monkey, that's not a decision that some\Npersonal you made. That happens of its
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.76,0:31:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,own. So that's trained. That's trained.\NSo these things are trained. They're
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.91,0:31:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,impersonal.\NExperiencing and watching is also
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.72,0:32:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,impersonal.\NIt's a phenomena occurring of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.88,0:32:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see we we begin withdrawing. It's\Nlike we draw back further and further
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.15,0:32:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,from mentalization\Nmore to the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.51,0:32:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So the field is watching experiencing\Nand we become aware that this is
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.08,0:32:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,impersonally happening within a field.\NThe self, the self is not the content.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.72,0:32:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The self becomes you become more aware\Nof the self
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.08,0:32:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,as the awareness.\NAnd the awareness is coming out of an
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.32,0:32:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,aspect of consciousness. The observer\Nwitnesser. The observer witnesser.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.96,0:32:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, we're we're we're moving the\Nsense of I
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.00,0:32:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,from I am that bad person\Nthat forgot to fill the gas tank and ran
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.96,0:33:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,out of gas. How could I be so stupid?\NSo the naive person identifies then with
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.76,0:33:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the content of thought itself.\NThe average person is at the effect is
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.76,0:33:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the victim of thinkingness.\NThe average person is
