Dialogue: 0,1:07:40.07,1:07:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no point to trying to focus on\Nthe moment and now in meditation. People
Dialogue: 0,1:07:43.44,1:07:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,say, I try to focus on now, but I can't\Nfocus on now. My mind is always thinking
Dialogue: 0,1:07:47.11,1:07:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,about the past or the future. I said,\Nwell, your mind is always thinking about
Dialogue: 0,1:07:49.92,1:07:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,the fast the past or the future right\Nnow, isn't it? So you're still in the
Dialogue: 0,1:07:52.79,1:07:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,now, even if you're thinking about the\Npast and the future.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:57.44,1:08:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,But now is just a label we put to a\Nspecific awareness
Dialogue: 0,1:08:02.40,1:08:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,because let's say because your awareness\Nhappens to be passing this point. It
Dialogue: 0,1:08:07.44,1:08:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,says this is now, this is now, this is\Nnow, this is now. But that's just a
Dialogue: 0,1:08:11.59,1:08:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,nominalization. Your mind just made that\Nup. There isn't any nowness going on,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:15.76,1:08:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,folks.\NBut let's not walk around saying we live
Dialogue: 0,1:08:19.52,1:08:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,in the now. It's a corruption of\Nreality.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:23.92,1:08:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody lives in any now. Show me the now\Nyou live in, idiot.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:29.75,1:08:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't live any then. You don't live\Nany future. You don't live any now
Dialogue: 0,1:08:33.19,1:08:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,either. All those are\Ntime dimensions. Those are all
Dialogue: 0,1:08:38.96,1:08:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,durations. Those are all depictions.\NThose are all nominalizations which
Dialogue: 0,1:08:45.12,1:08:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,arise up in here. You see, you got to\Ngive it a name. Why do you have to give
Dialogue: 0,1:08:49.52,1:08:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,a name to whatever is at this second?\NYou see, and when you get to a certain
Dialogue: 0,1:08:55.92,1:09:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,level, you don't even call it is\Nanymore. That's also an absurdity.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:00.31,1:09:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,There's neither is nor is not.\NThe conundrum at age three
Dialogue: 0,1:09:08.88,1:09:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,was existence versus non-existence.\NHere's this horrible little body and
Dialogue: 0,1:09:13.83,1:09:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,this rotten little wagon\Nand instantly comes the fear.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:20.15,1:09:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,First of all, the kid couldn't think in\Nwords. This is all non-verbal.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:25.67,1:09:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But awareness is aware of this\Nexistence.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:32.31,1:09:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Along with existence came instantly fear\Nof non-existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:38.00,1:09:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It was apparent that if one is, it could\Nhave come about that one is not would
Dialogue: 0,1:09:44.31,1:09:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,not have been. You know what I'm saying?\NIf you could be, it could have happened
Dialogue: 0,1:09:49.19,1:09:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,that\Nyou're coming into beingness wouldn't
Dialogue: 0,1:09:53.52,1:09:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,have happened in which case you wouldn't\Nbe
Dialogue: 0,1:09:58.40,1:10:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,at age three. I'm puzzling existence\Nversus non-existence. A fear of
Dialogue: 0,1:10:02.88,1:10:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,non-existence.\NOh boy. Oh boy. So the first thing
Dialogue: 0,1:10:07.52,1:10:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,existence does is give you a fear of\Nnon-existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:11.04,1:10:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We see that in the ego is concerned with\Ndeath.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:15.84,1:10:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,If things dies, it's not going to exist\Nanymore, folks. No such thing's going to
Dialogue: 0,1:10:21.12,1:10:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,happen.\NNo such luck.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:25.12,1:10:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You not go from existence to\Nnon-existence. You just go to a
Dialogue: 0,1:10:28.08,1:10:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,different style of existence in which\Nall these lifetimes string out as one
Dialogue: 0,1:10:31.60,1:10:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,lifetime.\NI went through a couple of them the
Dialogue: 0,1:10:34.64,1:10:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,other day. Oh my god, I just soon forget\Nthat all together.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:41.19,1:10:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,But it was\Nhow consciousness evolved through these
Dialogue: 0,1:10:46.40,1:10:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,various physical physical physicalities,\Neach one serving a very definite
Dialogue: 0,1:10:52.00,1:10:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,purpose. And as I say, they tended to\Nflip-flop. In this one, you did this and
Dialogue: 0,1:10:56.08,1:11:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the next lifetime you flip back again to\Nlike undo all that. Oh boy.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:01.84,1:11:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So\Nthe way out of all of that, the karmic
Dialogue: 0,1:11:11.28,1:11:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,constant.\NSee, because when you're in that
