Dialogue: 0,1:17:55.28,1:17:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,here's this kid out there with his\Nbooks, you know, and uh in those days,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:59.60,1:18:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, everybody sort of trusted\Neverybody. Now, nowadays, you think he
Dialogue: 0,1:18:02.80,1:18:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,was probably a killer or something, but\Nanyway, in those days, everybody trusted
Dialogue: 0,1:18:06.23,1:18:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody. So, the truck driver would\Npick up this kid staying out in the cold
Dialogue: 0,1:18:11.44,1:18:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,wind and snow, you know.\NBut the the idea of magic was of course
Dialogue: 0,1:18:17.92,1:18:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,that saying seven seven times and then\Nspinning about on my heels seven times
Dialogue: 0,1:18:22.23,1:18:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,was going to make this truck stop. You\Nknow
Dialogue: 0,1:18:26.00,1:18:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,of course when it did then I that\Nconnected the magic even stronger
Dialogue: 0,1:18:31.52,1:18:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and once in a while it wouldn't\Nwell
Dialogue: 0,1:18:36.56,1:18:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,still it happened a lot of the time but\Nyou see how you mind gives causality to
Dialogue: 0,1:18:41.44,1:18:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,it causality to it. All right. So we\Nwant to get out of that child's world
Dialogue: 0,1:18:46.40,1:18:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,then magical causality.\NThe world's belief in causality is
Dialogue: 0,1:18:51.84,1:18:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,really sort of magic living in the world\Nof magic
Dialogue: 0,1:18:55.92,1:19:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,because it doesn't see that what it\Ntakes to create every instant is the
Dialogue: 0,1:19:01.52,1:19:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,totality of God\Nas creation throughout all of time.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:09.28,1:19:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So we get out of being the content of\Nconsciousness. We become the context of
Dialogue: 0,1:19:14.48,1:19:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness. We become the reality out\Nof which consciousness arises.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:22.96,1:19:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll take a break.\N>> Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:34.48,1:19:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Hold this. Check over your thorus.\N>> I can't do it with my eyes closed.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:39.92,1:19:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,>> This is a good check. Resist.\NI was This is a bum check and I just use
Dialogue: 0,1:19:45.67,1:19:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,it for fun every time.\NSays insufficient funds anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:54.56,1:20:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Just for fun with kinesiology.\NWell, our picture is still crooked, but
Dialogue: 0,1:20:01.67,1:20:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,we've gotten used to it looking at it\Nthis way. And if we changed it, then
Dialogue: 0,1:20:06.32,1:20:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody have to look at it this way.\NThere must be some way to make it look
Dialogue: 0,1:20:11.60,1:20:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,straight. But anyway, we don't care\Nabout that. All right. I want to just go
Dialogue: 0,1:20:16.00,1:20:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,into a few more specifics about u\Nmeditation and handling
Dialogue: 0,1:20:20.71,1:20:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,content of mind and things to notice\Nabout it.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:26.15,1:20:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,If you sit in formal meditation and\Nfocus on the content of mind as it
Dialogue: 0,1:20:31.67,1:20:36.23,Default,,0,0,0,,passes by,\Nthe first thing you notice is it's it's
Dialogue: 0,1:20:36.23,1:20:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,irrational.\NUh it goes on and on
Dialogue: 0,1:20:40.80,1:20:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and then you'll begin to see that the\Nthe thinkingness
Dialogue: 0,1:20:46.48,1:20:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,is coming about\Nas a as as a result of several things.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:54.32,1:20:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Habit\Num boredom
Dialogue: 0,1:20:58.96,1:21:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and the idea that uh thoughts are\Nworthwhile that they serve a purpose. Um
Dialogue: 0,1:21:05.28,1:21:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,so they're they're entertainment.\NThey're going to solve problems. It
Dialogue: 0,1:21:08.56,1:21:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,gives you something. Thinkingness is\Nsomething you can do.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:12.88,1:21:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh people think thinking is worthwhile.\NI'm going to sit down and think about
Dialogue: 0,1:21:16.23,1:21:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that.\NBut when you're meditating, you're not
Dialogue: 0,1:21:20.00,1:21:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,you're not interested in what you're\Ninterested in is getting beyond thought.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:24.71,1:21:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a field of energy out of which\Nthinking is is arising.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:30.40,1:21:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And so I want to go into a specific\Ndetail about that. Let's say
Dialogue: 0,1:21:36.08,1:21:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,you're sitting in let's say you're\Nsitting in in formal meditation
Dialogue: 0,1:21:40.80,1:21:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and um the thinkingness is arising of\Nits own. You'll see it's arising of its
Dialogue: 0,1:21:47.60,1:21:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,own.\NIt's coming out of
Dialogue: 0,1:21:51.92,1:21:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,a desire to think.\NThe mind wants to think.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:58.32,1:22:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Um it's coming out of an energy\NIf you don't get caught up in the
Dialogue: 0,1:22:08.71,1:22:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,content of thought,\Nyou end up at a point of observation
Dialogue: 0,1:22:15.52,1:22:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,where the thinkingness arises and then\Nit passes away.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:20.00,1:22:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I think we said in a previous lecture\Nlike looking out a car window without
Dialogue: 0,1:22:24.88,1:22:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,focusing on what's going by, but looking\Nthrough the same point of the car
Dialogue: 0,1:22:29.19,1:22:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,window,\Neverything flicks by. You understand
Dialogue: 0,1:22:32.80,1:22:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,what I'm saying? You don't like fixate\Non on this and watch it and then fixate
Dialogue: 0,1:22:36.88,1:22:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,on the next. That's the way the mind\Nusually works. I mean the the Yeah, the
Dialogue: 0,1:22:41.19,1:22:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,mind and the eyes. It it looks at this\Nand then it follows it and then it
Dialogue: 0,1:22:45.84,1:22:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,clicks back this way and it clicks. He's\Nconstantly doing that.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:49.67,1:22:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Um\Nthere is a way of focusing on thought of
Dialogue: 0,1:22:54.32,1:22:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,not moving with the thought, not getting\Nabsorbed in the content, the emotion,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:58.96,1:23:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the story of it.\NJust witnessing from a fixed point of
Dialogue: 0,1:23:03.84,1:23:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,observation\Nthat the the thought arises
Dialogue: 0,1:23:09.52,1:23:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,a specific thought arises out of sort of\Nan amorphous potentiality
Dialogue: 0,1:23:15.44,1:23:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,to become a thought.\NIt gains greater and greater form. It
Dialogue: 0,1:23:20.63,1:23:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes very very specific. Crosses the\Npoint of aware of of attention
Dialogue: 0,1:23:27.44,1:23:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and begins to fade out fade out. It\Nloses form and disappears.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:36.48,1:23:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a form of meditation which\Nwhich requires
Dialogue: 0,1:23:40.80,1:23:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,one-pointedness of thought.\NThis is out of Zen training.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:47.84,1:23:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a fixity of intention of\None-pointedness of mind. The focus soap
Dialogue: 0,1:23:55.60,1:24:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,like a razor\Non the edge of this moment of focus.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:01.19,1:24:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So the thought arises like a like a note\Nof music arises crests. No sooner does
Dialogue: 0,1:24:08.63,1:24:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the note of music crest than the music\Nis already fading away.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:15.52,1:24:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You become aware with this fixity of\Nintention and focus
Dialogue: 0,1:24:22.96,1:24:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,that that which is the self is prior to\Nthe thought
Dialogue: 0,1:24:28.15,1:24:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that that which one is arises\Nfrom
Dialogue: 0,1:24:34.40,1:24:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,the source. You'll see all the thinking\Nthis is coming out of an energy
Dialogue: 0,1:24:39.60,1:24:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and one can begin to release the energy\Nof the desire
Dialogue: 0,1:24:46.23,1:24:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,to think.\NLet's see how that works. I haven't done
Dialogue: 0,1:24:51.04,1:25:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,it in some years.\NThis thought is arising
Dialogue: 0,1:25:03.84,1:25:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,out of um a formless energy field\Nuh which begins to gather form
Dialogue: 0,1:25:13.04,1:25:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes specific as a thought and then\Nfades away.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:18.15,1:25:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,One can by fixity of focus\Nfix on on the instant let's say we'll
Dialogue: 0,1:25:26.23,1:25:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,use the term instant on the process just\Nprior to its coming into form.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:34.71,1:25:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So in the beginning you start\Nthinking about old dog Rover and how he
Dialogue: 0,1:25:38.56,1:25:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,got a glaucoma in his left\Ncar bunkle and they had to take him to
Dialogue: 0,1:25:43.04,1:25:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the and then the anesthesia croaked and\Nthe family crying and good old Rover and
Dialogue: 0,1:25:48.96,1:25:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Christ now what are we going to do for a\Ndog? I mean you got this whole long
Dialogue: 0,1:25:52.08,1:25:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,story\Nas you meditate you get beyond that and
Dialogue: 0,1:25:56.80,1:26:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and you get to see Rover. Okay. I mean,\Nif you picture Rover's image,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:02.63,1:26:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a perhaps a slight memory, but\Nnow you get to Roverness itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:08.08,1:26:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, there's the essence of Roverness\Nwithout the whole freaky story that goes
Dialogue: 0,1:26:11.52,1:26:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,with Roverness. There's just the essence\Nof Roverness. And u now the name Rover
Dialogue: 0,1:26:18.40,1:26:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,disappears. You just focus on the\Nessence
Dialogue: 0,1:26:22.15,1:26:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,of that dog's beingness and his\Nlovingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:25.67,1:26:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You get to the heart of\Nwhat was Rover
Dialogue: 0,1:26:32.56,1:26:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and now the form is disappearing.\NYou're getting almost to dogness.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:39.76,1:26:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You're getting to animal relatedness.\NYou're getting to
Dialogue: 0,1:26:45.67,1:26:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,life identifying with life.\NYou're getting to an energy that is
Dialogue: 0,1:26:53.19,1:27:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,prior to the specific of thought itself.\NSo specific thoughts are coming out of
Dialogue: 0,1:27:00.88,1:27:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,like a little energy factory,\Nlittle energy source, an energy sink,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:05.92,1:27:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,whatever you call it.\NUm,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:10.00,1:27:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and one can surrender that to God. So\Nwhen it
Dialogue: 0,1:27:15.28,1:27:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,we didn't talk about renunciation yet\Nsurrender then is renunciation in that
Dialogue: 0,1:27:25.28,1:27:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,one eventually\Nlets go of the belief that one is the
Dialogue: 0,1:27:29.84,1:27:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,source of all that and sees that it is\Nhappening of its own.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:35.36,1:27:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,one gets lets go of the wantingness of\Nthinkingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:42.15,1:27:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Early in the game, you see that\Nthinkingness all has a payoff.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:46.71,1:27:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The way to silence that thinkingness is\Nto be willing to surrender the payoff of
Dialogue: 0,1:27:51.44,1:27:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,that thinkingness.\NThe sad stories,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:56.71,1:28:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the excitement,\Nthe erotic titilation, whatever is
Dialogue: 0,1:28:00.96,1:28:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,associated with that thought, the\Nwillingness to surrender that
Dialogue: 0,1:28:07.04,1:28:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the great pleasure of being right.\NJudgmentalism,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:16.40,1:28:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,righteousness.\NThe downfall of mankind since the
Dialogue: 0,1:28:21.28,1:28:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,beginning of time has been\Nrighteousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:24.23,1:28:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody feels righteous in what they\Ndo. Everybody that pulls the trigger on
Dialogue: 0,1:28:27.52,1:28:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,feel righteous.\NEvery war is based on righteous.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:31.04,1:28:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody's righteous. I don't want to\Nhear about people's rights and
Dialogue: 0,1:28:35.04,1:28:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,righteousness.\NGive me a break.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:44.96,1:28:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So, the mind wants to be\Nrighteous. It wants to manufacture
Dialogue: 0,1:28:48.40,1:28:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,self-pity,\Ngrief, mourning, anger, rage, delight,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:52.63,1:28:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,anticipation, fear.\NIt does a whole melodrama. One has to be
Dialogue: 0,1:28:58.32,1:29:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,willing to let go the payoff of these\Nego positionalities.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:04.88,1:29:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You first you discern what is the payoff\Nof that.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:10.08,1:29:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's the fun of hating those\Nidiots.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:15.19,1:29:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,We love to hate people. I mean, it's\Nfun, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:21.04,1:29:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,,They're bad and they deserve it. So\Nto start this mind, we we witness how it
Dialogue: 0,1:29:31.19,1:29:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,behaves. Then we see that it's being\Nsourced. It's being sourced by the
Dialogue: 0,1:29:35.92,1:29:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,payoff of this thinkingness.\NAs we get be as we we're willing to
Dialogue: 0,1:29:40.88,1:29:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,surrender the payoff to God, could you\Nlet go
Dialogue: 0,1:29:46.15,1:29:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the pleasure of self-pity and surrender\Nit to God? Could you? Yeah. Would you?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:51.19,1:29:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NSo, there's a constant of letgoingness
Dialogue: 0,1:29:55.19,1:30:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,of the payoff of this thinkingness\Nthat gives gives the thinkingness less
Dialogue: 0,1:30:01.36,1:30:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,of an emotional charge.\NThe willingness to surrender the payoff.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:08.32,1:30:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Each negative feeling\Nis not serving something else. It's
Dialogue: 0,1:30:13.67,1:30:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,serving itself. The payoff of guilt is\Nthat you get to feel guilty. The payoff
Dialogue: 0,1:30:18.71,1:30:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,of anger is you get angry.\NYou get to experience the payoff. The
Dialogue: 0,1:30:24.56,1:30:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,feeling is the payoff.\NPeople say, "What what do people get out
Dialogue: 0,1:30:29.12,1:30:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,of hate?" Well, you get hatred, man.\NWhat do you think? That's why we killed
Dialogue: 0,1:30:33.92,1:30:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,all those kids at school. Bang. Bang.\NBang.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:37.92,1:30:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The gratification is the feeling itself.\NYou see, our society can't find the
Dialogue: 0,1:30:44.08,1:30:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,answer anything because it's always\Ntrying to psychologize everything and
Dialogue: 0,1:30:47.28,1:30:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,look for the reason in childhood.\NThere's no reason in childhood. It's the
Dialogue: 0,1:30:52.40,1:30:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,glee of it now.\NWatch the TV the in the Middle East
Dialogue: 0,1:30:58.23,1:31:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,throwing rocks at each other. This side\Nthrows rocks at this side. They're
Dialogue: 0,1:31:01.36,1:31:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,really getting off on that. This side\Nthen throws rocks on that side. They get
Dialogue: 0,1:31:05.28,1:31:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,off on that, too. Now they both get\Nindignant. Boy, they're all hot with
Dialogue: 0,1:31:09.44,1:31:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,indignity. Then they pull both pull out\Nrifles and they shoot away at each other
Dialogue: 0,1:31:13.19,1:31:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and then throw bombs and then they send\Nin tanks and blast away.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:17.67,1:31:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody gets on TV about the poor\Nlittle infant, the poor mother crying.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:23.12,1:31:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole melodrama is such a huge\Npayoff, man. How can you resist it?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:30.00,1:31:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So the mind gets sucked into it and it\Ncan't get out. You don't have to look
Dialogue: 0,1:31:33.92,1:31:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,for something from childhood to explain\Nit. The payoff is in the instant of now.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:40.15,1:31:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It's right now is the payoff.\NThe payoff of rage is you get to feel
Dialogue: 0,1:31:46.40,1:31:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,rage.\NWatch those people throwing rocks at
Dialogue: 0,1:31:51.44,1:31:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,each other. There it's a state of high\Nglee,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:55.67,1:31:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,isn't it?\NIt's got nothing to do with their
Dialogue: 0,1:31:59.04,1:32:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,childhood. It's got nothing to do with\Npolitics. has got nothing to do with
Dialogue: 0,1:32:01.84,1:32:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,America being richer and all that crap.\NThey just love an excuse to throw rocks.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:12.00,1:32:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So the payoff is the experience itself.\NIn meditation, we have to be willing to
Dialogue: 0,1:32:19.36,1:32:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,surrender the payoff of the experience\Nitself to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:26.15,1:32:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Lord God, out of my worship of thee, my\Ndesire and love to reach
Dialogue: 0,1:32:31.92,1:32:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and to be of service,\NI'm willing to relinquish the payoff of
Dialogue: 0,1:32:37.60,1:32:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,this emotionality so that I can get\Nbeyond it. That's it.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:43.60,1:32:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So that way the thinkingness has less of\Nan emotional charge because as long as
Dialogue: 0,1:32:48.08,1:32:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,you're getting off on the charge of the\Nemotion of the thinkingness, it's not
Dialogue: 0,1:32:53.67,1:33:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,going to stop.\NIf you can reduce the emotion behind it
Dialogue: 0,1:33:00.88,1:33:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,now, it slows down and it becomes more\Navailable for inspection.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:06.80,1:33:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So a great deal of what's done in formal\Nmeditation at least in Zen style. One
Dialogue: 0,1:33:11.76,1:33:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,pointedness of mind is inspection. One\Ninspects the phenomena of thinkingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:18.48,1:33:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We know that the minute you inspect the\Nthing, it already changes.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:26.23,1:33:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Um\NMr. Gdatara Mahara said that that when
Dialogue: 0,1:33:31.44,1:33:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,you start observing the mind it already\Nbegins to change out of observation.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:39.12,1:33:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Observation. So the first thing that's\Nhappening in meditation is by the mere
Dialogue: 0,1:33:43.44,1:33:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,act of observation\Nyou're already altering the content of
Dialogue: 0,1:33:47.76,1:33:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness\Nby virtue of your intention.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:53.67,1:33:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,to get to the source of this\Nthinkingness. If you follow this track
Dialogue: 0,1:33:58.08,1:34:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,of onepointed fixity of observation,\Nyou'll get that all thinkingness is
Dialogue: 0,1:34:03.84,1:34:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,coming out of a little energy factory\Nlike a little source of a volcano
Dialogue: 0,1:34:10.96,1:34:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and one can surrender\Nthe onlogi of the thought before it
Dialogue: 0,1:34:16.80,1:34:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,takes form. As you keep letting it go,\Nit starts out with a story about oh good
Dialogue: 0,1:34:22.71,1:34:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,old Rover. As you let go that that whole\Nstory, it gets down to just a paragraph.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:28.40,1:34:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,As you let go the paragraph, it gets\Ndown to a sentence. Finally just gets
Dialogue: 0,1:34:32.48,1:34:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,down to the name Rover.\NThe willingness to to surrender the
Dialogue: 0,1:34:37.67,1:34:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,instant a thing arises in consciousness,\Nfinally even Rover starts to dissolve.
